The paper discusses the challenges faced by data scientists in preparing raw data for ML/AI and proposes a data-driven approach that relies on statistics and ML to extract insights from any data set in a domain-agnostic way. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of data exploration and processing steps, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents an end-to-end solution for data science, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
